===Noun===
{{en-noun|~|es}}

# {{lb|en|onomatopoeia}} A [[loud]] sound, like the crashing together of metal objects.
#: ''I heard a '''clash''' from the kitchen, and rushed in to find the cat had knocked over some pots and pans.''
# {{lb|en|military}} A [[skirmish]], a hostile encounter.
# {{lb|en|sports}} a [[match]]; a game between two sides.
#* {{quote-text|lang=en|year=2011|author=Tom Fordyce|title=Rugby World Cup 2011: England 12-19 France|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/rugby_union/15210221.stm|passage=But they ran out of time and inspiration as Les Bleus set up a deserved semi-final '''clash''' with Wales.}}
# An angry [[argument]]
# Opposition; contradiction; such as between differing or contending interests, views, purposes etc.
#: ''a '''clash''' of beliefs''
#: ''a personality '''clash'''''
# A [[combination]] of garments that do not look good together, especially because of conflicting colours.
#: ''She was wearing a horrible '''clash''' of red and orange.''
# {{lb|en|hurling}} An instance of restarting the game after a "dead ball", where it is dropped between two opposing players, who can fight for possession.
# {{lb|en|Scotland}} [[chatter|Chatter]]; [[gossip]]; [[idle]] [[talk]].

